item.dc:creator: @ImpromptuXpk ImpromptuXpk
item.description:
@ImpromptuXpk wrote:

ultraking x2:

i changed my jdk version, but it still don’t works, still shows the same error…

You have to change your environment variables.

  1. Right click on “My computer” and select the “Properties” option.
  2. Go to “Advanced system settings”
  3. Click on “Environment Variables”
  4. Under the “Path” variable, enter the location of the bin in the JDK you downloaded. For example, mine is “C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_16\bin;” (without the quotes). Just change the JDK version to the version you have and you should be good to go.

item.dc:creator: @stevenlin598 stevenlin598
item.description:
@stevenlin598 wrote:

it means that you didn’t edit the bat files.
Go to runserver.bat.
Left click it.
If your using a different mouse then hold control and then click it.
Click edit
You should see something like C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_19\bin\javac.
You change the jdk.1.6.0_19 to the version of java you have. So if you have version 20 then you would replace it to
C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_20\bin\javac
hope it helped you!
